Nggilari in a letter addressed to state chairman of the party, Alhaji Ibrahim Bilal, said his withdrawal, was based on reasons known to him. He, however, maintained his unflinching loyalty to the party. Nggilari who defected to APC in 2020, lamented that his former party, PDP was not fair to him. The former governor, was the second to aspire for Adamawa North senatorial zone. Also former governor Boni Haruna, aspired for same the position under the platform of PDP, equally withdrew from the race few days to the commencement PDP primaries.